gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 125, Bucks 90
gameRecap.excerpt: The Warriors defeated the Bucks, 125-90. Stephen Curry led the way for the Warriors with 29 points (6-10 3pt. FG), eight rebounds and five assists, while Draymond Green added 12 points (2-4 3pt. FG), six rebounds and six assists in the victory. Giannis Antetokounmpo (23 points, seven rebounds, six assists) and Damian Lillard (20 points, 5-10 3pt. FG, six assists) combined for 43 points for the Bucks in the losing effort. The Warriors improve to 33-28 on the season, while the Bucks snap a six-game winning streak and fall to 41-22.
